"(max-width: 2560px) 100vw, 2560px\" data-src=\"/portfolio/assets/static/background.42db587.d05441d5b1af5e36c152f6e02eac56bb.png\"><noscript><img class=\"g-image g-image--lazy g-image--loaded\" src=\"/portfolio/assets/static/background.42db587.d05441d5b1af5e36c152f6e02eac56bb.png\" width=\"2560\"></noscript></p>\n<h2 id=\"project-description\"><a href=\"#project-description\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"icon icon-link\"></span></a>Project Description</h2>\n<p>While searching for a good project to work on for this year's Hacktoberfest event, I happened to walk by a co-worker's desk who had been using a custom theme on his Mattermost instance. I thought his theme looked pretty cool, but I quickly came to realize that there was no easy way for two users to share themes, nor a central place where I could \"shop\" for new ones for myself either.</p>\n<p>This is how I decided to make my own unique contribution to the Mattermost ecosystem, by filling a void that had long been neglected in making full use of Mattermost's customizeable theme interfaces.</p>\n<p>For this relatively simple project, I decided to make an attempt to explore as many topics I had been unfamiliar with as possible. So I invited a fellow developer (<a href=\"https://github.com/josephk96\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">@josephk96</a>) to help contribute to this project. I also made sure to employ the usage of functional components in React for the project, and in the event that a component was to be stateful, to make use of React hooks instead of utilizing class-based components with lifecycle methods and constructors.   </p>\n<p>I made sure to set a rule for the repository where a PR can't be merged without at least 1 reviewer's approval, to force both myself and my fellow developer to get used to going through PR review workflows (as we work at a firm that only maintains software, there isn't much to \"review\" here).   </p>\n<p>Once the project began to look presentable, I deployed it to GitHub Pages, and set up GitHub Actions that would automatically build and deploy the project to GH Pages whenever the <code>master</code> branch was merged (i.e. a PR was accepted).</p>\n<p>Once the project was announced on the official Mattermost community server, the project was very well received by the Mattermost team, where they immediately showed us their appreciation and started showing off which themes they had picked for their workspace</p>\n<p><img class=\"g-image g-image--lazy g-image--loading\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml,%3csvg fill='none' viewBox='0 0 2120 864' xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg' xmlns:xlink='http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink'%3e%3cdefs%3e%3cfilter id='__svg-blur-cded874100939f3915c73c27f9be1225'%3e%3cfeGaussianBlur in='SourceGraphic' stdDeviation='40'/%3e%3c/filter%3e%3c/defs%3e%3cimage x='0' y='0' filter='url(%23__svg-blur-cded874100939f3915c73c27f9be1225)' width='2120' height='864' xlink:href='data:image/png%3bbase64%2ciVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAEAAAAAaCAYAAAAHfFpPAAAACXBIWXMAABYlAAAWJQFJUiTwAAAGAklEQVRYhd1YS28cRRDeHwB%2b7O7svHump2fn/dhdbIUgFJIAIqAIAkIIRwIlF045JIecECIoNyKOcOGABDf%2b5Ieqx%2bUdb8aOjbAxHL6t6uqenp3qr6qre2SaJvqYzWYXAp7bsiz4vg/XdY9Jz/OOjbssjOjFjuPoP8J/5qJA7yJZliWSJNEyTVNUVaXb9D8u8v1DGM3ncyyXS1RViTzPEQQBhBBH8p8Grzo5gyXjIt53IoJOjsgB8TxBpGLtBP5jffDq8QoS%2bGP6%2btDH9vWhMedx3JEu/LPhtNV3PPiej5FlO7jz7k08uH%2bAoqw1C4iSBKJoURQIwxBxHGsopTQ7%2bs4YovlJ/WcNk5PaR/AG2pu2jQUg6fmezjNWHcCNBUYzy8K3Tx7jz19%2bwPXrK%2bR5gbqu0batluQE%%2b0AmSrIIkaYRAhJZhHCnG0KMo87e64QphEC6i8UwkxpXWZxN7ZQkHGkcwlRm%2bUQmP59ncOIn%%2bbZzvMDSeTnFzr8HBo88xX3X7PGV%2b%2bnBKQOQM3gZpV9Cl82FVSOBihXUqmrhi7I/jNmdsavNc/Wc2n6cxfTuD7Tw2UnMs6hh3b8WwnTVDN8v6PoMty8KIj6hjewbbc7Bou3KYCyDW%2bfRGOmVtLlJ43GDh0iunqc2nPwLbKWNzP8/Nc5HO4/jd/TKdd4iiyJFmFW69VeLpVxkCnexeHf8WOUCfv80ZjImhq6aHH89RpBKu%2b3Im3Yz9fntIP238eXHSXGu7q1d%2bOjv7qdJiBlAcUcOYGQhENyklPU58JD2X9WFKXRWQI/i/vwqmaWK0vbWF7589xx%2b//ob9vb2u5j%2bszYmGfEkxswNMDetSb2su5UZod2cbD795hB%2bfP0FbhHCF0kmKE01XVkZ48FmNN5chdnYNWBvXa